	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002234_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<lb/><p rend="center"><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>23 March 1865 </p><!-- TRANSC: headed notepaper not displayed:
<p><placeName>Newstead Abbey</placeName> <lb/><placeName>Mansfield</placeName> <lb/><placeName>Notts</placeName></p>
-->
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p>No 3. is most like 
<lb/>what is wanted - 
<lb/>the stone is placed 
<lb/>sloping away 
<lb/>from the person 
<lb/>grinding. She has the 
<lb/>rule so far under 
<lb/>her as to give her 
<lb/>weight to the move
<lb/>able stone. It is 
<lb/>placed on a mat 
<lb/>or skin to catch 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002234_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>the meal as it slips off 
<lb/>at the lower end<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>Put a <choice><sic>killt</sic><corr>kilt</corr></choice> on 
<lb/>from waist to knees 
<lb/>above that bare 
<lb/>with a string of beads 
<lb/>on the neck - neat 
<lb/>hands are usual 
<lb/>in the originals - 
<lb/>You might make 
<lb/>a front view 
<lb/>like 3. &amp; a side 
<lb/>one - the knees 
<lb/>being right at the 
<lb/>high part of the stone<reg>.</reg>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002234_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/>Make a good face &amp; 
<lb/>head. Don<reg>'</reg>t follow 
<lb/>the usual formula 
<lb/>namely - Mouth like 
<lb/>that of a hippopotamus 
<lb/>Ears like waggon- 
<w>-<lb break="no"/>wheels</w> - no forehead 
<lb/>&amp; nose like the 
<lb/>droppings of a 
<lb/>cow and you 
<lb/>will oblige<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Yours &amp;c 
<lb/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002234_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/><!--<pb n="04"/>-->

